    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>NGC3783 B7 HCN(4-3) &amp; HCO+(4-3)</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We aim at observing the HCN(4-3) and HCO+(4-3) line with an SNR = 10 in the peak of the line. This allows for recovering the kinematics on the small scales of 0.035"-2" that we are interested in. The line flux has been estimated using a radiative transfer model of the AGN environment (CAT3D) in combination with the CLOUDY photoionization code. The continuum flux was estimated from modelling the 1-100micron high-angular resolution SED plotted in Hoenig et al. 2013.

