        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>In order to spectrally resolve the line for kinematic studies, we require a moderately good resolution (few km/s) for the estimated line widths (FWHM) of 300 km/s. Therefore we chose the bandwidth that covers the full width, has the shortest observing time demand, and also use averaging to decrease band rate.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The dusty environment of AGN has sizes typically of the order of &lt;50 pc. In NGC3783, this corresponds to &lt;0.25". Therefore, we are interested in the smallest scales that can be achieved with ALMA and that coincide with our VLTI infrared interferometry and a small field of view is sufficient. As a result we ask for the 0.035" resolution mode.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We aim at observing the HNC(4-3) line with an SNR = 10 in the peak of the line. This allows for recovering the kinematics on the small scales of ~0.035"-0.5" that we are interested in. The line flux has been estimated using a radiative transfer model of the AGN environment (CAT3D) in combination with the CLOUDY photoionization code. The continuum flux was estimated from modelling the 1-100micron high-angular resolution SED plotted in Hoenig et al. 2013.

We ask for standard calibration.

This results in a total time request of 1.06 hours for this science goal.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
